    "body": "### Neovim Version\n\n`0.6` nightly, happens as far back as `0.3.4`\n\n### Operating system/version:\n\nWSL Ubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version:\n\nmintty 3.4.5\n\n### TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vim\r\nset cmdheight=2\r\n\r\nfunction! Foo() abort\r\n  let prompt = \"hello\\nworld: \"\r\n  call input(l:prompt)\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nfunction! Bar() abort\r\n  echo \"hello\"\r\n  let prompt = \"world: \"\r\n  call input(l:prompt)\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nautocmd CmdlineEnter * call timer_start(0, {-> 1})\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Scenario 1: Type `:call Foo()<CR>`\r\n- Scenario 2: Type `:call Bar()<CR>`\n\n### Vim\n\nYes, Vim 8.2 (patch `1-3273`) has the expected behavior\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBoth scenarios should show\r\n```\r\nhello\r\nworld:\r\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nOnly\r\n```\r\nworld:\r\n```\r\nis visible.\r\n\r\nThis happens when the number of lines of output from `echo` and the prompt is less than or equal to `cmdheight`.",
